Date: Wed 12 Dec 2007
From: Michael Woodford <mhwoodford@yahoo.com>


Re: Babesiosis, tigers - India (Bhopal)
---------------------------------------
About 15 years ago I went to Bannerghatta National Park, near
Bangalore to see some sick, captive tigers that had been recently
imported from UK. Blood smears revealed _Trypanosoma evansi_,
probably acquired from the cow meat they were being fed or from
biting flies, of which there were many. Treatment with suramin
(Antrypol, ICI) was successful.

--
Michael Woodford
<mhwoodford@yahoo.com>

